oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: City Drug Store window displays
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photographs of the front window displays at City Drug Store in Mount Pleasant. An advertisement for Rexall dyspepsia tablets covers the center of the window. Note: on the same negative below MA298 is an image labeled MA299. The image, however, shows a different view of the store from that of negative MA299/ID# 10230.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Window displays; Drugstores
